   "source": [
    "2) Make a distinction between NAT Gateways and NAT Instances.\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "Network Address Translation (NAT) allows resources in private subnets to connect to the internet, other VPCs and on-premise network. They can communicate with services outside the VPC, but cannot receive unsolicited connection requests.\n",
    "NAT has two ways i.e. NAT Gateways and NAT Instances and the differences are:\n",
    "\n",
    "i) NAT Gateway is fully managed by AWS while NAT Instance is created and managed by user.\n",
    "ii) NAT Gateway is highle available and is created in each Availability Zone to ensure Zone independent architecture while NAT Instance uses script to manage failover.\n",
    "iii) NAT Gateway bandwith can scaled upto 45 Gbps while NAT Instance bandwidth depend on instance type\n",
    "iv) NAT Gateway Maintenance is managed by AWS while in NAT Instance it is managed by user.\n",
    "v) In NAT Gateway, software is optimized for handling NAT traffic while in NAT Instance, a generic AMI is configured.\n",
    "vi) In NAT Gateway, cost is dependent on the number of gateway used, duration of usage and amount of data sent through it whereas in NAT Instance, cost is dependent on number of instance used, duration of usage, type and size of instance.\n",
    "vii) In NAT Gateway, an Elastic IP is chosen to associate with public NAT Gateway at creation whereas in NAT Instance, Elastic IP or public IP is chosen.\n",
    "viii) When a connection times out, a NAT Gateway returns an RST packet to any resources behind the NAT gateway that attempt to continue the connection whereas a NAT Instance sends a FIN packet to resources behind the NAT instance to close the connection."
   ]
  },
