    "3) Describe the essential components of Amazon Web Services (AWS).\n",
    "\n",
    "Ans:\n",
    "The Essential components of AWS are:\n",
    "i) IAM: Identity and Access Management is a free web servcie of AWS which is the heart of AWS security because it helps to control the access of identities like user, group or role by the help of policy. It authenticates and authorizes the users to use service and resource of AWS. It safeguards the user account and provides a centralized control for the AWS account for administering the principals.\n",
    "\n",
    "ii) Elastic Compute Cloud or EC2: EC2 is a web service of AWS that provides resizable computing capacity as per the demand of the load. It helps developer to focus on building and deploying application and not worry of the infrastructure.\n",
    "\n",
    "iii) Simple Storage Service or S3: Amazon S3 is simple object storage device that allows huge amount of data storage and retrival from anywhere from the internet. It provides developers highly scalable, reliable, fast and low cost data storage infrastructure.\n",
    "\n",
    "iv) Simple Email Service: It can be used to send transactional email to thousands of users at a single go, which is not available in Outlook or Gmail.\n",
    "\n",
    "v) Amazon Route 53: Route 53 is a DNS (Domain Name Service) web service which helps to connects user requests to AWS infrastructure such as Amazon EC2 instances, Elastic Load Balancing load balancers, and Amazon S3 buckets, as well as infrastructure outside of AWS.\n",
    "\n",
    "vi) Cloud Watch: It is used to track and collect metrics, set alarms, collect and monitor log files, and also monitor resources such as EC2 instances, RDS DB instances, and DynamoDB tables.\n"
   ]
  },
